<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
    
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>We have been highly commended in a category of the inaugural ‘Analysis in Government Awards 2020’ held online on 8 December 2020.</p>

<p>There were 5 separate categories for these awards, in a competition which had been organised by the Government Analysis Function.</p>

<h3 id="pension-scheme-stakeholders">Pension scheme stakeholders</h3>

<p>The team from the Government Actuary’s Department (GAD) was highly commended in the ‘communication’ category and was one of four teams which were shortlisted.</p>

<p>This recognition was for our work to support Public Service Pension Scheme (PSPS) stakeholders on how the McCloud remedy could affect different groups of scheme members. Other shortlisted teams for the same award were from the Office for National Statistics, and NHS England and NHS Improvement.</p>
<figure class="image embedded"><div class="img"><img src="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/image_data/file/110959/Comunication_category_AF_awards_960x640.png" alt="Analysis Function Awards - Communication"></img></div></figure>

<h3 id="highly-commended">Highly commended</h3>

<p>The Head of PSPS, Jan Claisse said: “We are so proud to have been nominated for these inaugural awards from the Government Analysis Function, let alone to be highly commended. This achievement is significant due to the fact there were well over 100 nominations.</p>

<p>“It’s a tribute to the hard work of people in a range of roles across GAD who helped contribute to this project around the impact of the McCloud judgment.”</p>

<h3 id="further-information">Further information</h3>
<p>Further details of GAD’s work in this area can be found on our website -  <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/special-feature-gad-support-for-mccloud-remedy" class="govuk-link">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/special-feature-gad-support-for-mccloud-remedy</a></p>
</div>

</div>
